# GRADIent ENcoder Decoder (GRADIEND) 
> Jonathan Drechsel, Steffen Herbold

[![arXiv](https://img.shields.io/badge/arXiv-2502.01406-blue.svg)](https://arxiv.org/abs/2502.01406)

This repository contains the official Python package for [GRADIEND: Monosemantic Feature Learning within Neural Networks Applied to Gender Debiasing of Transformer Models](https://arxiv.org/abs/2502.01406).

## Start here

- Documentation start page: [docs/index.md](docs/index.md)
- Tutorials (workflow-first): [docs/index.md](docs/index.md#tutorials)
- Pruning guide (manual masks, pre-/post-pruning): [docs/index.md](docs/index.md#pruning-guide)
- API reference (auto-generated): [docs/index.md](docs/index.md#api-reference-auto-generated)
- Examples overview: [docs/index.md](docs/index.md#examples-supplemental)

## Installation

### Basic Installation

Install the core GRADIEND package:

```bash
pip install gradiend
```

### With Experimental Features

For helper functions for data preparation, analysis of encoder/decoder, printing of LaTeX tables and plots, and example code:

```bash
pip install gradiend[experiments]
```

### From Source

```bash
git clone https://github.com/aieng-lab/gradiend.git
cd gradiend
pip install -e .
# Or with experiments:
pip install -e ".[experiments]"
```

## Quick Start

### Basic Usage

```python
from gradiend import ModelWithGradiend

# Load a base model with GRADIEND
model = ModelWithGradiend.from_pretrained(
    "model-base-cased",
    latent_dim=1,  # Single feature dimension
    use_gradients=True
)

# Encode text using gradients
text = "The doctor went to the hospital."
label = "he"
encoded = model.mask_and_encode(text)
print(f"Encoded value: {encoded}")

# Modify the model using GRADIEND
modified_model = model.modify_model(
    learning_rate=1e-4,
    feature_factor=1.0,
    part='decoder'
)
```

See `examples/basic_usage.py` for a complete example.

### Training a GRADIEND Model

Training requires a `Setup` class that defines your data and evaluation. For experimental setups (gender debiasing, race/religion debiasing), install with `[experiments]`:

```python
from gradiend.setups.gender.en import GenderEnSetup
from gradiend.trainer import train_gradiend

setup = GenderEnSetup()
train_gradiend(
    setup=setup,
    model="model-base-cased",
    output="results/models/model-base-cased-gradiend",
    epochs=1,
    batch_size=32
)
```

## Package Structure

### Core Package (`gradiend`)

The core package provides the essential GRADIEND functionality:

- **`gradiend.model`**: Core model classes
  - `GradiendModel`: The encoder-decoder model (weights-only)
  - `ParamMappedGradiendModel`: GradiendModel + param map for base-model gradients
  - `ModelWithGradiend`: Wrapper combining base model with GRADIEND
  - `AutoModelForLM`, `AutoTokenizerForLM`: Model loading utilities

- **`gradiend.training`**: Training functions
  - `train()`: Low-level training function
  - `train_all_params()`: Train on all params
  - `train_multiple_params()`: Train on specific params
  - `TextGradientTrainingDataset`: Dataset for training

### Experimental Features (`gradiend[experiments]`)

When installed with `[experiments]`, additional features are available:

- **`gradiend.setups`**: Predefined setups for common tasks
  - `GenderEnSetup`: Gender debiasing setup for English
  - Race and religion setups

- **Setup-based evaluation**: Encoder/decoder analysis and metrics live in setup packages
  - `gradiend.setups.core`: `get_model_metrics`, `plot_topk_neuron_intersection` (topk_venn)
  - `gradiend.setups.text`: LM evaluation (`evaluate_mlm`, `evaluate_clm_perplexity` in `lm_eval`), decoder helpers in `decoder_utils`

- **`gradiend.export`**: Export functions
  - LaTeX table generation
  - Plotting utilities
  - Result export functions

## Documentation

